## Query Key Factory Pattern

```typescript
userKeys = {
  all:      ["users"]                           // invalidate everything
  lists:    ["users", "list"]                   // all list queries
  list:     ["users", "list", {page, size, role}] // specific filtered list
  details:  ["users", "detail"]                 // all detail queries
  detail:   ["users", "detail", userId]         // specific user detail
}
```

This enables **granular cache invalidation**:
- After **create**: invalidate `lists()` (refetch all list pages)
- After **update**: invalidate `detail(id)` + `lists()`
- After **delete**: invalidate `lists()` + remove `detail(id)`

