## Key Architectural Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Feature-based folder structure** | Each feature encapsulates all 4 clean architecture layers, making features self-contained and independently maintainable |
| **Repository pattern on frontend** | Abstracts HTTP layer from business logic; allows swapping API implementation (e.g., for tests) |
| **Use Cases as classes** | Mirrors backend pattern; provides a clear, testable unit of business logic per operation |
| **Redux for UI-only state** | Modals, forms, selections don't belong in server cache — Redux handles ephemeral UI state |
| **React Query for server state** | Automatic caching, background refetching, optimistic updates, retry logic |
| **Optimistic updates with snapshots** | Instant UI feedback; full rollback on error using snapshot/restore pattern |
| **Error cache (create mutation)** | Prevents re-sending requests that already failed with 400/409/422 within a 30s window |
| **Query key factory** | Structured, hierarchical keys enable precise cache invalidation |
| **Barrel exports (index.ts)** | Clean public API per feature — consumers import from `@/features/users` instead of deep paths |
| **Next.js rewrites as API proxy** | Avoids CORS issues in development; single origin for frontend + backend |
